# Place your macOS ARM64 JRE here

Extract a JDK 25 (or compatible) JRE into this folder so it looks like:
  jre/mac/Contents/Home/bin/java

On macOS, a JDK distribution is a .jdk bundle (a directory).
Copy or symlink the entire .jdk contents here.

Example using Adoptium JDK 25:
  cp -R /Library/Java/JavaVirtualMachines/jdk-25.jdk/* jre/mac/

The launcher will resolve the binary at:
  jre/mac/Contents/Home/bin/java
